WEBVTT

00:04.308 --> 00:07.094
[wind whooshing]

00:07.268 --> 00:09.618
♪

00:11.315 --> 00:12.882
[bird cawing]

00:19.889 --> 00:21.238
Tag! You're it!

00:21.325 --> 00:22.587
I'm gonna get you!

00:28.680 --> 00:30.639
♪

00:39.082 --> 00:40.431
[soft crunching nearby]

00:40.649 --> 00:43.043
[squelching]

00:48.874 --> 00:53.096
[crunching, squelching continue]

01:02.627 --> 01:05.456
♪

01:12.159 --> 01:13.290
[twig snaps]

01:21.516 --> 01:23.953
♪

01:25.737 --> 01:27.478
[all panting]

01:39.751 --> 01:41.536
FORA:
Children.

01:46.845 --> 01:49.413
It seems as though one of you
took something of Ms. Myrtle's

01:49.587 --> 01:51.415
while playing in
the woods today.

01:51.589 --> 01:53.722
Who would like to speak up?

01:56.725 --> 01:57.943
May I?

02:07.692 --> 02:09.999
[sighs]

02:11.000 --> 02:14.134
There once was a mother

02:14.221 --> 02:17.224
with a beautiful child,

02:17.398 --> 02:20.575
who was taken from her

02:20.662 --> 02:25.406
by women both visceral and vile.

02:25.580 --> 02:30.411
They wore white
for their purity,

02:30.585 --> 02:35.242
with dark hearts
that burned bright,

02:35.329 --> 02:38.419
when they cast her
out of the town

02:38.593 --> 02:43.685
and whispered lies out of spite.

02:43.859 --> 02:47.384
And the people of the village
turned their backs

02:47.471 --> 02:50.082
to ignore the sole person

02:50.257 --> 02:54.435
who had ever deemed
their town worth more.

02:54.652 --> 02:57.394
And now...

02:57.481 --> 03:00.876
that woman would give her life

03:01.093 --> 03:03.835
to take back
what is hers,

03:04.009 --> 03:07.839
but she cannot do it

03:08.013 --> 03:10.842
unless you give back

03:11.016 --> 03:13.584
what is not yours.

03:21.026 --> 03:22.724
So...

03:22.898 --> 03:25.248
if one chooses

03:25.466 --> 03:28.904
not to speak,

03:29.078 --> 03:31.733
and say what you know...

03:31.907 --> 03:35.302
Well, then...
your place

03:35.389 --> 03:39.828
on this Earth
you must now forgo.

03:41.873 --> 03:42.831
[cane thudding loudly]

03:47.836 --> 03:49.838
♪

03:55.583 --> 03:58.020
[exhales]

04:08.073 --> 04:10.467
♪

04:20.608 --> 04:21.957
Anything?

04:22.174 --> 04:23.611
We just searched Icarus Hall

04:23.785 --> 04:24.786
and the surrounding woods.
No sign of Temperance.

04:24.960 --> 04:26.570
Or her free-spirited
prisoner, Lev.

04:26.744 --> 04:28.006
They're not at the
Historical Society

04:28.180 --> 04:28.877
or the tunnels
down below, either.

04:29.094 --> 04:30.487
Okay, so,

04:30.574 --> 04:32.184
we know that Temperance
doesn't just

04:32.402 --> 04:33.969
want Charity's soul
to have a family reunion

04:34.186 --> 04:35.797
with the daughter
who despised her.

04:35.971 --> 04:38.234
According to Charity's note
to Cora Dow,

04:38.408 --> 04:40.018
Temperance has a bigger plan.

04:40.192 --> 04:42.891
Yeah, the same plan that got her
banished from Horseshoe Bay.

04:43.065 --> 04:45.197
Maybe if we can figure out what
Temperance's larger plan is,

04:45.372 --> 04:47.025
we can figure out where
she's hiding Lev.

04:47.199 --> 04:48.157
Okay, well, the only thing
I've found out

04:48.331 --> 04:49.767
regarding Temperance's
master plan

04:49.941 --> 04:52.161
was her letter to Charity

04:52.335 --> 04:54.032
and that creepy map
with the blood

04:54.206 --> 04:55.164
leading to the Youth Center.

04:55.251 --> 04:57.209
We should, uh, all split up.

04:57.427 --> 04:59.516
W-We'll cover more ground
that way.

04:59.603 --> 05:01.039
NANCY: I can search
Icarus Hall.

05:01.213 --> 05:02.824
Maybe it takes another
screwed-up Hudson

05:02.998 --> 05:06.218
to find a family clue from
the original screwed-up Hudson.

05:06.393 --> 05:07.916
Hey, you are not
a screwed-up Hudson.

05:08.090 --> 05:09.961
Eh, I don't know.

05:10.048 --> 05:11.963
I just feel like I'm always
two steps behind Temperance.

05:12.137 --> 05:13.748
You're not alone in this.

05:15.445 --> 05:18.013
I mean, I can go with you
to Icarus Hall.

05:18.187 --> 05:22.496
Maybe find a clue to implement
in my genealogy algorithm.

05:22.670 --> 05:25.673
And then we can finally be
two steps ahead of Temperance.

05:25.847 --> 05:28.066
Find the last person
containing Charity's soul.

05:28.240 --> 05:30.242
[door opens, closes]

05:30.417 --> 05:31.418
PARK: Good!
You're all here.

05:31.592 --> 05:33.463
ACE:
Ah, we gotta fix that bell.

05:33.681 --> 05:35.422
BESS: What, still no sign
of Lev or Temperance?

05:35.509 --> 05:37.641
I had my team search
Temperance's Westchester home.

05:37.815 --> 05:39.034
She's still MIA.

05:39.251 --> 05:41.210
In the meantime,
why don't I

05:41.297 --> 05:42.516
accompany you two
to Icarus Hall?

05:43.734 --> 05:45.214
Outstanding.

05:45.301 --> 05:47.172
We'll take our own cars.

05:53.614 --> 05:55.398
Ooh.
I gotta...

05:57.313 --> 06:00.360
Uh... Ugh.
Customers will be here soon.

06:11.632 --> 06:13.895
Okay, so, uh,

06:14.069 --> 06:15.244
I haven't exactly
told my sisters

06:15.418 --> 06:17.289
that we're broken up yet.

06:17.507 --> 06:20.249
Okay, look, I'm sorry--
I overreacted.

06:20.336 --> 06:21.468
What, and that
make-out session was you

06:21.642 --> 06:23.470
trying to get back together?GEORGE: No.

06:23.644 --> 06:25.515
Oh, my gosh, no.
I just...

06:25.689 --> 06:27.778
I wanted Charlie to still think
that we are a thing.

06:27.996 --> 06:29.867
Ha. Okay.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.739
Look, being with you,

06:31.956 --> 06:33.436
that was the first time
that Jessie, Ted and Charlie

06:33.654 --> 06:35.699
have ever seen a healthy,
stable relationship.

06:35.873 --> 06:37.658
They are going to take
the news really hard.

06:37.875 --> 06:40.095
I don't want to lie to them.Okay, you won't have to.

06:40.269 --> 06:41.270
[phone chimes]I swear I'll tell
them tonight. Okay?

06:41.444 --> 06:43.664
Okay, Nancy says
that Carson and Ryan

06:43.881 --> 06:45.579
are parking their cars
out front.

06:45.753 --> 06:47.015
She wants us to keep them
out of her hair

06:47.189 --> 06:48.669
until we find Temperance.

06:48.886 --> 06:50.061
Okay, how about you and Nick

06:50.148 --> 06:51.715
help with
the Temperance manhunt,

06:51.802 --> 06:53.064
and I will keep an eye
on Ryan and Carson.

06:54.457 --> 06:57.112
I will have my overdue
sister chat.

06:57.329 --> 06:58.505
BESS:
Okay, good, that's great.

06:58.679 --> 07:01.116
We can research the
Historical Society for...

07:01.290 --> 07:02.378
Yeah, yeah.
Uh, I'll meet you there.

07:02.552 --> 07:04.119
I just gotta
make a quick stop.

07:04.336 --> 07:06.338
Nothing like an impromptu
kiss from your ex

07:06.556 --> 07:08.253
to send you flying
out the door.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.299
[door opens]Ah!

07:10.473 --> 07:12.083
Hello, Mr. Drew and Ryan!

07:12.257 --> 07:13.694
Wow, fancy
seeing you here.

07:13.911 --> 07:15.347
Uh, what can I get
you two today?

07:15.522 --> 07:17.524
Whatever caffeinated drink
you just chugged.

07:17.611 --> 07:20.004
CARSON: And two bowls of your
world-famous chowder, please.

07:20.091 --> 07:21.963
Dad-bonding lunch?

07:22.137 --> 07:23.660
We were prepping
for Ryan's discovery hearing

07:23.747 --> 07:26.184
for Everett's trial
and got a craving.

07:26.358 --> 07:27.664
Well, legal talk
always goes better

07:27.751 --> 07:29.927
with some award-winning
New England chowder.

07:30.101 --> 07:32.974
[quietly]:
Hey. You have got this.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.715
Thank you.

07:34.889 --> 07:37.282
♪ Hey, hey, hey. ♪

07:44.115 --> 07:46.553
Where are you, Temperance?

07:49.425 --> 07:51.688
Why are you out here
looking for Temperance?

07:54.952 --> 07:57.085
Hey. You have been
acting suspicious all week.

07:57.259 --> 07:58.347
What is going on?

07:59.870 --> 08:01.611
What are you keeping
from us, Nick?Okay, there are

08:01.785 --> 08:03.091
things going on that it's better
that you don't know about.

08:03.265 --> 08:04.309
For everyone's safety.

08:04.527 --> 08:05.702
Who is "everyone"?

08:08.879 --> 08:11.273
Oh, my God. Temperance
is threatening the kids.

08:11.360 --> 08:13.101
Oh, my God.Bess. Bess!

08:13.318 --> 08:15.538
Bess!

08:15.756 --> 08:17.714
Hey, kids, is everything
all right?

08:17.801 --> 08:19.194
Just checking in.

08:19.411 --> 08:20.674
Yep.Mm-hmm.
We're good.

08:26.027 --> 08:26.941
Oh, my God.

08:29.465 --> 08:30.553
Temperance has put
a hex on the kids.

08:30.727 --> 08:32.773
Don't say it out loud!

08:32.990 --> 08:33.991
I can call Nancy,
she can...

08:34.209 --> 08:35.210
No! No, no, no, no.
I'm trying not

08:35.427 --> 08:36.646
to let anyone
find out about this.

08:36.864 --> 08:37.778
Well, it's a little bit late
for that.

08:37.995 --> 08:39.823
[sighs]

08:39.997 --> 08:41.564
Okay.

08:41.782 --> 08:44.959
You... Do you, do you remember,

08:45.046 --> 08:46.830
uh, the-the artifact
that Tyler was looking into

08:47.004 --> 08:48.702
behind the Youth Center?Mm-hmm.

08:48.876 --> 08:51.661
Well, Temperance told me
that it's a supernatural seal

08:51.835 --> 08:53.402
covering up a tear
in the Veil between

08:53.489 --> 08:55.839
this world
and the darkness below.

08:55.926 --> 08:57.232
She's been waiting
200 years to open that veil.

08:57.449 --> 08:59.234
Yeah, and what she wants
on the other side of that seal

08:59.408 --> 09:00.844
is very, very bad.

09:01.018 --> 09:02.803
[whimpers][knocking]

09:06.458 --> 09:07.634
Hey, buddy.Hey, Nick,

09:07.808 --> 09:09.853
um, I think I just got bit
by a nasty bug.

09:09.940 --> 09:12.377
Got any first aid? It won't
stop itching and burning.

09:12.595 --> 09:14.031
When did the itching start?

09:14.249 --> 09:16.033
Just now while you and Bess
were talking.

09:16.251 --> 09:18.906
BESS: Oh, my God.
I think the hex heard us.

09:27.044 --> 09:28.742
♪

09:42.843 --> 09:45.585
[grunting]

09:49.632 --> 09:52.026
Oh, this can't be good.

09:53.636 --> 09:55.682
[footfalls echoing]

09:59.076 --> 10:01.688
The effects of Resting Powder
are never pleasant.

10:09.478 --> 10:12.829
Oh!
[panting]

10:16.093 --> 10:17.486
Who are you?

10:17.660 --> 10:19.706
Temperance Hudson.

10:19.880 --> 10:21.664
This will all be over soon.

10:21.882 --> 10:23.492
For everyone.

10:23.579 --> 10:26.408
After Nancy accepts
her town's fate.

10:27.278 --> 10:28.889
[grunts]

10:31.935 --> 10:34.068
[phone buzzing]

10:35.678 --> 10:37.898
Bess, it's getting worse.

10:38.072 --> 10:39.943
Okay, so, I did find the symbol.

10:40.117 --> 10:42.511
Um, "the dui circuli
typically indicates

10:42.598 --> 10:44.339
the presence of the Debrevhex."

10:44.556 --> 10:46.471
There is a footnote.

10:47.951 --> 10:49.692
It says the symbol
can also represent

10:49.910 --> 10:51.389
hundreds of other hexes.

10:51.563 --> 10:52.956
Temperance chose a hex

10:53.043 --> 10:54.305
that would be impossible
to narrow down.

10:54.392 --> 10:56.133
It's okay.
We're gonna figure this out.

10:56.307 --> 10:59.223
You still have the art easels
at the Youth Center, right?

11:00.529 --> 11:03.358
There has to be something in
here that gives us some insight

11:03.532 --> 11:05.360
into Temperance's master plan.

11:05.577 --> 11:07.101
Odds are it's hidden
in plain sight

11:07.188 --> 11:10.278
since we've all been here before
and never zeroed in on it.

11:10.452 --> 11:13.629
[Nancy sighs]

11:13.803 --> 11:15.936
I can't believe
I ever trusted Temperance.

11:16.110 --> 11:18.503
This place screams
"villain's lair."

11:20.375 --> 11:21.985
Definitely has a vibe.

11:22.159 --> 11:24.858
I just let a huge threat
walk around, unchecked.

11:25.075 --> 11:26.947
Hey.

11:28.644 --> 11:32.996
She played on your emotions
and your maternal relationships.

11:33.170 --> 11:35.912
You do everything you can
to protect this town.

11:39.742 --> 11:42.223
About what you told me
last night...

11:42.397 --> 11:44.704
Hey, I think you should
look at this!

11:54.626 --> 11:56.411
The, uh, mortar
around that stone

11:56.585 --> 11:58.805
is about a quarter of an inch
thicker than the rest.

12:07.161 --> 12:09.903
ACE:Classic.

12:13.558 --> 12:15.343
What is it?

12:15.560 --> 12:17.649
ACE:
Like, a bone?

12:17.824 --> 12:19.564
I've never seen
that language before.

12:23.090 --> 12:24.352
I have.

12:27.007 --> 12:31.011
At an orphanage
that was abandoned in 1971.

12:41.456 --> 12:43.414
Ah, damn it.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.373
It should be right here.

12:47.157 --> 12:49.029
Kids are always
screwing around in this place.

12:49.203 --> 12:51.596
The police tossed it
the last time we were here.

12:58.603 --> 13:00.170
What is that?

13:02.694 --> 13:04.609
A mystery for another day.

13:04.827 --> 13:06.307
We should fan out,

13:06.481 --> 13:09.049
look for the
bone fragment.Uh, yeah.

13:14.881 --> 13:18.101
Why can't anything be simple?

13:18.188 --> 13:22.279
Complexity makes an eventual
win that much more satisfying.

13:22.497 --> 13:25.195
And is that the goal?

13:25.369 --> 13:27.110
To be satisfied?

13:27.284 --> 13:29.678
If you're into
that sort of thing.

13:29.765 --> 13:33.987
Personally, I think
satisfaction is limiting.

13:35.510 --> 13:39.470
[sighs]
So is contentment.

13:39.557 --> 13:41.124
Or security in
what's familiar.

13:41.298 --> 13:45.172
I think those things
tend to keep you

13:45.389 --> 13:49.002
from seeing options that
are right in front of you.

13:51.091 --> 13:53.093
Like what?

13:53.920 --> 13:57.880
ACE:
Hey-o! Found it.

13:58.098 --> 14:00.100
NANCY:
Oh, nice.

14:00.274 --> 14:02.102
Has the same weird
writing on it.

14:02.319 --> 14:05.975
The breakage point
looks the same.

14:07.585 --> 14:09.544
Can you decipher the writing?

14:09.718 --> 14:11.894
NANCY: No.
But I know someone who might.

14:16.420 --> 14:19.989
Okay. So, with the symptoms
the kids have shown so far--

14:20.163 --> 14:24.515
the two-circle mark, the skin
irritation, the itchiness,

14:24.602 --> 14:27.301
and the fact that the hex
hasn't killed them yet--

14:27.388 --> 14:30.086
I was able to narrow it down
to these four candidates:

14:30.173 --> 14:32.045
the Malti,the Debrev,

14:32.219 --> 14:34.395
the Prynsipiaand the Bonnafis.Okay.

14:34.569 --> 14:36.353
And you can perform a ritual
to get rid of any of these?

14:36.571 --> 14:38.486
Technically, yes.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.531
But we still have to figure out
which hex we want to break.

14:40.705 --> 14:42.272
Right, okay.

14:42.490 --> 14:45.972
Um... Whoa.

14:46.059 --> 14:48.409
It's this hex. Right?
Headaches are a symptom.

14:48.583 --> 14:50.846
And Talia's got a headache.

14:51.020 --> 14:53.327
Have any of the other kids
had headaches?

14:53.414 --> 14:55.764
Well, no, but maybe they're
just trying to tough it out.

14:55.938 --> 14:57.592
I-I bet you it's the Malti.

14:57.809 --> 15:00.160
Okay, I think that
your desire to solve this

15:00.377 --> 15:01.596
is making you rush
a little bit.

15:01.813 --> 15:03.380
What's the alternative?

15:03.554 --> 15:05.948
Wait for Temperance to flip
the death switch on these kids?

15:06.166 --> 15:07.819
Of course not...I built this Youth Center

15:08.037 --> 15:09.821
so these kids
would have a safe space.

15:10.039 --> 15:13.608
And now, now I'm the reason that
their life might be in danger.

15:13.782 --> 15:17.394
Okay. You're right.

15:17.568 --> 15:19.135
It is definitely worth a try.

15:19.222 --> 15:20.397
Right.

15:20.615 --> 15:22.573
I'll prepare the ritual.

15:22.660 --> 15:24.575
Thank you.Okay.

15:43.072 --> 15:46.075
Come on, Bess. You can do this.

15:46.249 --> 15:49.209
BESS:
Cursed agent
from darkness beyond,

15:49.426 --> 15:52.473
sent from an enemy
with ill intent,

15:52.647 --> 15:54.910
your work is now at an end,

15:55.084 --> 15:59.219
and I call on you now to return
from whence you came.

16:08.880 --> 16:12.797
Not exactly the denouement
I was expecting. Okay.

16:15.452 --> 16:16.366
What happened?

16:16.584 --> 16:17.889
I don't know.

16:18.107 --> 16:20.066
TALIA:
Hey, my itch went away.

16:20.153 --> 16:22.111
[kids murmur agreement]Yeah. Mine, too.

16:22.329 --> 16:23.460
Hey, the kids
stopped scratching.[laughing]

16:23.634 --> 16:25.245
It worked.[chuckles]

16:27.595 --> 16:29.597
[gasps]

16:29.814 --> 16:31.207
BESS:
Oh, my God.

16:33.905 --> 16:35.168
I chose the wrong hex.

16:42.697 --> 16:45.482
Hmm. They're antlers.
From a silver stag.

16:45.656 --> 16:47.093
Very rare.

16:47.180 --> 16:49.269
Thought only to appear
every 400 years

16:49.486 --> 16:51.184
during the vernal equinox.

16:51.358 --> 16:53.316
You can tell by
the spiral pattern just there.

16:53.490 --> 16:54.622
The Women in White
believed that the antlers

16:54.839 --> 16:56.711
carried mystic abilities.

16:56.885 --> 16:59.279
And the writing?DARLENE:
I recognize it.

16:59.453 --> 17:00.889
It's a language
the Women in White used

17:00.976 --> 17:02.804
during their rituals
way back in the day.

17:02.891 --> 17:04.240
But I'm not fluent.

17:04.327 --> 17:06.112
Do any of the words
look familiar?

17:06.199 --> 17:08.940
The only thing
I can make out is...

17:09.115 --> 17:12.683
"Bring forth"
something "within."

17:12.770 --> 17:14.990
I think I have a book
somewhere in the basement

17:15.164 --> 17:17.166
that has a cipher
for the language.

17:17.340 --> 17:19.516
Forgive me.
I just moved into this place.

17:19.734 --> 17:20.865
But if you give me

17:21.083 --> 17:22.519
a few minutes,
I can find it.

17:22.693 --> 17:24.913
No problem. Thank you.

17:25.087 --> 17:26.088
Hmm.

17:26.262 --> 17:28.003
[phone buzzes]

17:28.177 --> 17:30.875
Boston field office.
Excuse me.

17:31.093 --> 17:33.095
Agent Park.

17:39.275 --> 17:41.103
[sighs]

17:41.277 --> 17:43.105
I've been avoiding
talking to you.

17:43.279 --> 17:45.325
Really?Mm-hmm.

17:47.979 --> 17:51.331
Well, sometimes
a person's got to avoid.

17:53.985 --> 17:57.728
But for what it's worth,
I don't regret what I told you.

17:59.687 --> 18:01.732
Whatever comes of it.

18:04.518 --> 18:07.825
Being in the liminal space
gave me some...

18:07.999 --> 18:12.134
perspective
on my life, so...

18:12.308 --> 18:15.746
when you're ready
to not avoid...

18:17.531 --> 18:19.272
...I'll be here.

18:23.624 --> 18:25.713
GEORGE:
See? I told you CarMax
would have plenty of options.

18:25.930 --> 18:27.193
Here, what do you think?

18:27.367 --> 18:28.933
Ooh! Jungkook
has one of these.

18:29.151 --> 18:31.110
He's Nick's favorite.
Get the SUV.

18:31.197 --> 18:34.809
Uh, what about
something smaller?

18:34.983 --> 18:36.593
You know, for, like,
just us four Fan girls.

18:36.767 --> 18:38.813
Look. Super cozy.

18:38.987 --> 18:40.423
Or three Fan girls
and Nick.

18:40.597 --> 18:42.425
Which three Fan girls?

18:42.599 --> 18:44.558
I think we both know.

18:44.645 --> 18:47.996
No, seriously, Charlie,
which-which three Fan girls?

